          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Vorga Superstar!!!!!</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.20)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=21805">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=6010">Andrew "cfbnv" Harwell</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=6010&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Actually, Vorga is just one of three Cald magi that work together to create a strong theme of Burn, Burn, and more Burn.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> February 27, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi:<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(544)">Ven</a><br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(543)">Raega</a> <br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(536)">Braggle</a>, Fireball, <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(677)">Vorga</a> <br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a>)<br>
<br>
Creatures (14) <br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(536)">Braggle</a> - 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a> - 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(537)">Er<a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a></a> - 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(373)">Raxis</a> - 1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(370)">Magma Hyren</a> - 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(807)">Tweave</a> - 3<br>
<br>
Spells (16): <br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(548)">Firefly Swarm</a> - 3 <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a> - 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a> - 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(550)">Wildfire</a> - 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(790)">Beam of Light</a> - 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(680)">Lava Flow</a> - 1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(357)">Storm Cloud</a> - 2<br>
Fireball - 2<br>
<br>
Relics (9): <br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(652)">Rayje&#39;s Belt</a> - 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a> - 3<br>
Gorgle&#8217;s Glasses - 2 <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(678)">Abraxin&#39;s Crown</a> - 2<br>
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Deck Note:<br>
 As MN Random pointed out, the deck is only forty cards (my bad!!).  As he also suggested, add another Raxis. <br>
<br>
 First and foremost, this is a spell-oriented deck for those who like to play with fire.  Each magi was specifically chosen to accentuate the theme of direct damage, and the creatures chosen were purely auxillery.<br>
<br>
General Notes:<br>
<br>
One of the main strategys of this deck is to set up a defense creature or two, and from behind them you want to burn every creature in sight.  This deck is very effective at doing so, but it takes practice to know which burn spells to use when.  For instance, Firefly Swarm is useful mainly for its ability to stop a creature from attacking, and should not be used to kill a 2 energy creature like Fireball or Lava Flow.  <br>
<br>
For larger creatures, you will want to Syphon Vortex as much energy from them as possible, and/or Storm Cloud + Scroll of Fire them to death.  Wildfire and Thunderquake are excellent for large armies, and Beam of Light can clear out a few creatures that survive those spells.  The creatures selected were selected because they were cheap, cost-effective, and had useful abilities.  Braggle is a Monster, and he can block and keep the opponent off turn after turn.<br>
<br>
Tweave doesn&#39;t have to be in a weave deck to use surprise, and 3 energy for free is always nice.  Arbolits cost 1 but still force the opponent to waste a resource on them, and only in dire situations should Arbolits be sacrificed for healing flame.  Ergars are beautiful in combination with everything in the deck, i.e. Storm Cloud and all burn spells.<br>
<br>
The relic selection is somewhat obvious; Rayje&#39;s Belts lock down things like Suppress on Sorreah, or abilities that protect creatures from spells.  Scroll of Fire is key to a burn deck, and Gorgle&#39;s Glasses can net you insane amounts of cards in the long run.  With Abraxin&#39;s Crown, you can finish of the magi with the same spells you used to finish off the creatures.<br>
<br>
The first magi was Ven, and he was chosen for many reasons.  Where I play, the general strategy against any and all Cald decks is build up a couple of creatures to massive amounts of energy to keep them out of burn range.  I play against Cald this way, my playtest partners play against Cald this way, and people I play against on the internet have a tendency to play this way.  Ven stops this defense cold, as any creature which spends spells and/or powers to pump itself up will go right back down when Ven gets through with it.<br>
<br>
Ven was also chosen because of his 14 starting energy- one of the highest starting energys for Cald magi.  This does not mean that you nessecarily want to go first, but if you are forced to you won&#39;t be stuck with 12 or 10 or something like that.  Another important aspect of Ven is his ability to stall with a Braggle.  Since his power allows creatures to gain OR lose energy, you can pump up that blocking Braggle whenever it gets too low, and you have a strong wall only susceptible to direct removal spells.<br>
<br>
Raega hits the board with 16 energy- a dismal number.  Her true power lies in her ability- a shockwave (more or less).  Her power can be very potent in removing a creature who&#39;s blocking your attack, or especially cheap after a Thunderquake or Wildfire.  She starts with the all-powerful Braggle, which can instantly set up a wall from which she can fling flame safely.  The only strategic problem with Raega is getting trigger happy and using her power all the time, essentially squandering all her energy.<br>
<br>
Vorga is last, and let me tell you from experience she is a powerhouse.  With all the burn in this deck, her power ends up allowing you destroy whichever creature you chose, and she can pick relics as well- a very versatile magi.  She starts at 18 energy- fairly high for a Calderan.  She also starts with a Scroll of Fire, an excellent card at any point in the game.  Her stable energy and strong power should help you finish off your opponent.<br>
<br>
Most match-ups are played in the same way, as afore mentioned.  Try to go second as often as possible so you know what you are up against before you play a creature, and so Ven gets 19 energy.  If you have any questions about the deck, d-mail me.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
-Andrew   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=21805"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21805" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
